# Infrastructure

## Rules

- Single Pulumi stack for all infrastructure. Add new services as component functions in `src/`.
- No `gcloud` CLI for infra manipulation — use the Pulumi stack.
- Hardcode project constants (VPC name, subnet CIDR, secret names, instance counts) in code. Only externalize values that truly vary.

## Structure

- `src/config.ts` — stack configuration and secrets.
- `src/services.ts` — GCP API enablement.
- `src/project.ts` — VPC, Artifact Registry, CI identity, Cloud Build IAM.
- `src/user_service.ts` — Cloud Run, secrets, runtime identity, custom domain mapping.

## Config & Secret Policy

- `Pulumi.prod.yaml` holds non-secret config. Secrets are added via `pulumi config set --secret`.
- Local/dev secrets: `.env` files (e.g. `user-service/.env.dev`, committed).
- `user-service/.env.prod`: prod DB URL for migrate/studio (gitignored).

## Custom Domain

When `userServiceEnableCustomDomain` is true, creates a Cloud Run domain mapping (free, no load balancer or reserved IP). Set a CNAME in DNS pointing to `ghs.googlehosted.com`.
